cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it addresses the task of camera pose estimation from raw image pixels. It may also belong to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category as camera pose estimation is a crucial task in robotics. The use of deep neural networks suggests that it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the experimental results on the Cambridge Landmark dataset suggest that it may also belong to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category.
